Parents, we have exciting news to reduce the amount of hard copy paperwork required to be turned into the school . We have gone digital for many of our forms that you had to fill out by hand. Filling out these forms for this year is as simple as clicking a few buttons on our website. You can also submit absence excuses, as well as request early dismissals for doctor appointments etc.
There are 3 forms that need to be completed that you can find in your Parent Portal. Sign in to your Portal account here: https://curwensville-sapphire.k12system.com/CommunityWebPortal/Welcome.cfm
The Parent Portal is also where you will submit absence excuses. There are detailed instructions on the … More

post_text:
The Curwensville Area School District will be using the NFHS Network to broadcast all home Jr. High, Junior Varsity and Varsity athletic events. The camera equipment for the broadcasts is scheduled to be installed on Sept. 17th with our first broadcast scheduled for Sept. 18th.
Parents/fans can sign up for the service for a fee at: https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/schools/curwensville-area-high-school-curwensville-pa
Once signed up, you will be able to watch all home Curwensville athletic events remotely as well as any other school that is also using the service and many of our area school districts are also registered through NFHS. You will be able to search for schools to see if they are included and also watch past archived events.

Let’s take a moment to honor our “attendance warriors” from last school year. These students fought their way through all kinds of obstacles and earned a ton of respect as a result! Also worthy of a strong shout out is George Pry of Horace Mann Insurance Agency. He was gracious enough to donate gift cards to each of our warriors for their efforts! Today’s video honors our gang using a cult-classic movie as inspiration. All the cool guys, especially those who are over 40, will dig this!

Roll Tide!

Chris Marsh
Elementary Principal
Curwensville Area School District

post_text: Fall sports athletic physicals will be performed on Wednesday July 22nd for only those who turned their forms in by 7/15/2020. Students with the last name starting with A through E 8:00 am to 9:30 am; students with the last name starting with F through H 9:30 am to 11 am; students with the last name starting with the letters I through P 12 noon to 1:30 pm; students with the last name starting with Q through Z 1:30 pm to 3:00 pm. All students will enter at the high school office and will be required to wear a mask. If you do not have a mask one will be provided for you.

post_text:
Select Choir presents “Mid-Summer Choir Tour”

The silence of the arts in the Curwensville area has officially come to an end. Come to the Clearfield Riverwalk Amphitheater at 5:00pm and/or Irwin Park in Curwensville at 7:30pm on Friday, July 17th to hear the Curwensville Select Choir present their “Mid-Summer Choir Tour” concert, a resurgence of what they would have performed for you all in the spring! From contemporary standards to historical treats, there is guaranteed to be something for everyone! Our students (and recent graduates!) are chomping at the bit to get back to what they love and we cannot be more excited.

We thank the Curwensville Area School District and the Curwensville Music Boosters for their generosity in sponsoring this first-of-its-kind event for Curwensville. We hope you come out to celebrate with us!

Digital Media Arts at Clearfield County CTC
June 9 at 12:16 PM ·

Briana Swindell and Dominic Kovach, recent graduates from the Digital Media Arts program, just passed the exam to earn the Adobe Certified Associate (ACA) certification in Visual Design using Adobe Photoshop 2020 today.

The ACA certification is an industry-recognized credential that effectively validates one’s expertise in the Adobe Creative Cloud suite. Those who possess the ACA certification can confidently prove that they have the skills and knowledge to meet the demands of today's design industry.

Congratulations Briana and Dominic!!!

LAST CHANCE TO ORDER YOUR HIGH SCHOOL YEARBOOK FOR 2019-2020

Hello. On behalf of the Echo staff, we want to inform you that your final opportunity to purchase a 2019-20, high school yearbook is quickly approaching. We would hate to see you miss out on all the unforgettable moments from this past year.

Students, order your yearbook as the deadline for sales is May 31st. Seniors, don’t forget to order the book that captures your final high school memories. Thank you to all those who have already purchased and to those still ordering . . . WE ARE GOING FOR THE GOLD!

If you have any questions you can email dpennington@curwensville.org.
Here is the link to order a yearbook.
https://yearbookforever.com/

"Today, Friday, May 29th, we would have gathered at 7:00pm to celebrate the Curwensville Class of 2020 with our traditional Baccalaureate service. While this pandemic has temporarily closed some doors this year, including an in-person service, it has also opened new ones permanently. The Curwensville Ministerium, in collaboration with the school district, decided to create a virtual Baccalaureate service this year, collecting videos from faculty, staff, students, and members of the Ministerium. It is our hope that even though we will be in our homes, that this Baccalaureate service is equally meaningful, if not more, as it always has been. Please use the attached program to follow along! Congratulations Class of 2020!"

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DhbV21LXn6s

5-27-20

Summer Meals:

We are pleased to announce that we will continue to distribute meals throughout the summer, through the Summer Food Program.

Meals will be bagged and may be picked up at the HS Office entrance door # 5 on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays from 11am until 1pm. beginning on Monday June 8th and will continue through Friday, August 21st.

Mondays will be breakfast and lunch for 2 days.
Wednesdays will be breakfast and lunch for 2 days.
Fridays will be breakfast and lunch for 3 days.

Any children 18 years of age and younger may obtain a meal without charge.

post_text:
I would like to offer a sincere “thank you” to our staff that prepared, loaded and distributed 3450 breakfasts/lunches this morning for the long Memorial Day weekend. I wouldn’t be able to get all of the names that stepped in during a time of need to assist, but witnessing it was another reminder of the pride of the Curwensville family and it warms my heart.

The road since March 13th has been a bumpy one and keeping an eye looking positively forward can be challenging for anyone. We are blessed with some truly amazing people in this family and we will continue to support one another, work together and come out stronger.



I wish each of you the best this Memorial Day weekend…



Ron

Updated Lunch information

Meals will be delivered to all elementary bus stops on a 2hr delay morning run schedule every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.

Our school site pickup will be available Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 11am to 1pm.

Regardless of grade/age students may obtain meals at any location.

Just so you are aware of our meal schedule for the rest of the school year.

Bus runs/site pickup:

Tomorrow - Friday, May 15 (3 days of meals)

Monday, May 18 (2 days of meals)
Wednesday, May 20 (2 days of meals)
Friday, May 22 (5 days of meals)

Monday - Closed - Memorial Day, May 25
Wednesday, May 27 (2 days of meals)
Friday, May 29 (3 days of meals)

Monday, June 1 (2 days of meals)
Wednesday, June 3 (2 days of meals)
Friday, June 5 (3 days of meals)

Beginning Monday, June 8, we will continue to offer meals. How that will look has not been finalized yet. We will update you as that comes to fruition.

post_text:
Pick up of Locker Items for Students in Grades 7-12:

• We are asking that you come to the school between 11:00 and 1:00 on your scheduled day. We will do this similar to chromebook pick-up. Please stay in your vehicle, just give us your name and we will bring your stuff to you.
• If you have siblings you may come on either scheduled day.
• If you have items in the, band, locker room or shop area you will be permitted to pick these items up as well
• If you are unable to come during your scheduled time due to ride limitations. Please email (bhayward@cuwensville.org), Mr. Kephart (mkephart@curwensville.org), or Officer Cramer (bcramer@curwensville.org) to schedule a pick up time.

Seniors: Monday, April 27th
Juniors: Tuesday, April 28th
Sophomores: Wednesday, April 29th
Freshman: Thursday, April 30th
8th grade: Friday, May 1st
7th grade: Monday May 4th

Alexander Starr‎Curwensville High School Alumni Association
April 16 at 2:34 PM ·

Hello everyone. I'm sure very few of you know, but I'm president of the Alumni Association. This year with the Covid Crisis, the alumni banquet among many, many other things has been cancelled. We are however still trying to collect donations in order to provide the graduating seniors with well-deserved scholarships. Attached is a letter requesting donations and where to forward them. I figured I would attach it here to see if anyone was interested in donating for this years seniors who will be missing out on a lot of stuff. Hopefully, scholarships won't be one of those things. Thank you all!

post_text: The Curwensville Area School District is accepting applications for an anticipated Full-Time Elementary Education Teacher beginning with the 2020-2021 school year. Interested candidates should send cover letter, standard teaching application, resume, all undergraduate and graduate transcripts, copy of PA Certificate, three letters of recommendation and current (within one year) Act 34, Act 114, Act 151, PDE Form 6004 and a Sexual Misconduct/Abuse Disclosure Release under Act 168 by mail to Deb Sloppy, Board Secretary, 650 Beech Street, Curwensville, PA 16833. Applications can also be emailed to jobs@curwensville.org. Applications will be accepted until noon on May 11, 2020.

Gardner’s Candy will be delivered in Curwensville on April 1, 2020 at Music Booster President, Brenda Daniel’s Home at 428 Bloomington Ave, Curwensville.

We will be holding pick up from 2:00 PM to 6:30 PM on that day. Please follow these instructions:

- Proceed past Brenda’s house to Fredricka Street - Turn left and proceed to the stop sign.
- Make a left down Station Street go to across the tracks and up the hill to Pennsylvania Avenue.
- Make a left there and drive up to where you see someone from the Music Boosters.
- Someone will take your name and deliver your products to you at your car from Brenda’s garage, and you can be on your way.

Our goal is for you to pick up and not get out of your car. You can visit another day please stay safe!!

If you need to make other arrangements please contact Brenda Daniel by calling or texting to 814-592-9191.

post_text:
The Financial Reality Fair for Seniors is a unique opportunity for students to experience some of the financial challenges they will face when they start life on their own.

It is a hands on experience in which students identify their career choice and starting salaries then complete a budget sheet requiring them to live within their monthly salary while paying for basics such as housing, utilities, transportation, clothing and food.

Students left today with a view into what costs they can anticipate and how to budget for the future. Thank you for all those that volunteered their time today to make this Reality Fair successful.

Who has the winning Golden Ticket?

Dear Curwensville Elementary School Families,

Who has the winning Golden Ticket?

Because we are partnering with SchoolStore, each student has been given a packet with a Golden Ticket number. One student at Curwensville Elementary School has a winning Golden Ticket!

Thank you to everyone who has already participated. However, as of this morning, our school has not yet had a winner. The winning ticket is still out there!

To see if your family has it, grab the packet your child brought home, go to schoolstore.net, and sign up for the program.

If you have not participated, the winning ticket may be in your hands. Please help us raise needed funds with this simple and safe email program by participating today. Your family may have the Winning Golden Ticket.

Thanks,
Chris Marsh

Curwensville Elementary Principal

shared_text:
Life Fast Forward
February 19 at 3:32 PM ·

Our speaker today at the Curwensville School Exploring program was Josh Kunkle, Mgr of Walmart Supercenter.

The Curwensville and St Francis 8th grade students had the opportunity to listen to Josh share real life experiences on various career paths as an employee at Walmart.

Josh has worked for Walmart over the last 21 years. He has been a store manager for 15 years. He also serves on the Greater Clearfield Chamber of Commerce Board.

The Chamber would like to thank Josh for speaking today. We would also like to thank District Attorney, Ryan P. Sayers for hosting our Exploring program.

All 3 students will be advancing on to participate in PMEA Region III Band in March!
